cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS

The paper deals with term weighting schemes in text categorization, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes novel approaches using supervised learning, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the experiments involve cross-classifier and cross-corpus evaluations, which suggest a focus on data science (cs.DS).
